rComments: Natalie is very enthusiastic and passionate about the course material. She also gives out easy participation grades for showing up to tutorials. Her grading scheme is very straight forward. She encourages students to see her during her office hours and provides helpful feedback.

She is very approachable and had a grading criteria that focused on actually holistically learning the concepts of the course as opposed to complete regurgitation. The final paper ensured that it somehow encompasses the whole course. You will definitely remember the things you learn in her course for a lifetime. And, she's really beautiful. :)
